In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims Peace Officers Memorial Day and Police Week in the United States. He acknowledges the bravery and sacrifice of law enforcement officers who work to maintain public safety and hold those who break the law accountable. The President emphasizes the importance of enhancing relations and trust between law enforcement and the communities they serve, in order to make policing safer and more effective. He states that it is within the power of the nation to make progress in this area and his administration is taking steps to implement recommendations for 21st century policing. President Obama calls upon all Americans to observe these events with appropriate ceremonies and activities, and for the flag to be flown at half-staff on Peace Officers Memorial Day.